<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;The 500 Smith &amp; Wesson Magnum is a natural progression of our leadership role in handgun development,&quot; said Roy Cuny, president and CEO of Smith &amp; Wesson Corp. &quot;Smith &amp; Wesson has a strong customer contingency of hunting and shooting enthusiasts that are continually looking to us for innovation. We produced the original Magnum(R) revolver with the introduction of the .357 Magnum in 1935 and 20 years later amazed the shooting world with the .44 Magnum. Now in 2003, we have once again produced a premier hunting revolver with no equal.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, this is not the .50 AE round that the Desert Eagle uses. This is the same diameter but longer. It's supposed to produce 2600 ft-lbs. of muzzle energy. If this helps any, the previous most powerful handgun cartridge (.454 Casull) was around 1800 ft-lbs muzzle energy.<br>
<br>
Counter-Strike kiddies will probalby spooge over this, but I imagine its only real use would be if someone crossbred tanks and Kodiak bears and tried to invade America. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=techfireblaster>techfireblaster</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://liquid2k.com/techfire6/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/15/03 1:45:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12023.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/manhattanproject/me.gif HEIGHT=87 WIDTH=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smith &amp; Wesson introduces stupid-huge handgun cartri</span><hr size=1> OMG, that f*ckin' kicks @ss!!!  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;"> An it Harm None, Do what ye Will </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
