<br>
actually lots of people hunt with handguns.  in fact several people in my fathers family actively hunt big game with a combination of rifles and heavy duty handguns like the guns talked about in this thread.  for them, it's the thrill of having so much power in just a hand gun that they love.<br>
<br>
at any rate, while i think that there should be some gun control laws, this type of revolver is made specifically for hunting very <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>large</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> animals (like they said, bears, moose and the like).  So there is a legitimate need, the same need that spurred the development of more and more powerful bores and calibers of handguns.  Given the size and expense of a weapon such as this, I doubt that your average punk on the street would ever use it to commit a crime, especially given that you could get a 'saturday night special' for less than $50 in some places...  so i think that this is pretty much a product aimed squarely at people (big game hunters) with specific, legitimate needs.<br>
<br>
